@page "/mapbox/token-help"

<PageTitle>BlazorMap — Mapbox access token</PageTitle>

<section class="demo-panel">
    <h1>Getting a Mapbox access token</h1>
    <p>
        Mapbox GL needs an <strong>access token</strong> (not strictly an “API key”, but the same idea: a secret string from your Mapbox account).
    </p>
    <ol class="demo-steps">
        <li>Create a free account at <a href="https://account.mapbox.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mapbox.com</a> if you don’t have one.</li>
        <li>Open the <a href="https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Access tokens</a> page in your Mapbox account.</li>
        <li>Copy your <strong>Default public token</strong>, or create a new token with the scopes you need for maps.</li>
        <li>In this demo project, paste the token into <code>wwwroot/appsettings.json</code>:
            <pre class="demo-inline-pre"><code>{
  "Mapbox": {
    "AccessToken": "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE"
  }
}</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Restart or reload the app and open the <NavLink href="/mapbox">Mapbox demo</NavLink> again.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        Official reference:
        <a href="https://docs.mapbox.com/help/getting-started/access-tokens/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mapbox — Access tokens</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        <NavLink href="/mapbox">← Back to Mapbox demo</NavLink>
    </p>
</section>
